    "description": {
      "es": "",
      "en": "Like substitute(), except that if placeholders are missing from mapping and kwds, instead of raising a KeyError exception, the original placeholder will appear in the resulting string intact. Also, unlike with substitute(), any other appearances of the $ will simply return $ instead of raising ValueError. While other exceptions may still occur, this method is called “safe” because it always tries to return a usable string instead of raising an exception. In another sense, safe_substitute() ma..."
